    <body>
      <section eId="sec_37_0903">
        <num>37-0903</num>
        <heading>Applicability</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_0903__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The requirements of this title shall not apply to\nhigh priority chemicals used in or for industry or manufacturing,\nincluding chemicals processed or otherwise used in or for industrial or\nmanufacturing processes and not included in the final product.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_0903__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Combustion. The requirements of this title shall not apply to\nhigh-priority chemicals generated solely as combustion by-products or\nthat are present in combustible fuels.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_0903__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Small business exception. The requirements of this title shall not\napply to children's product manufacturers that employ five persons or\nfewer and are independently owned and operated.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_37_0903__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Retailers. A retailer is exempt from the requirements of this\ntitle unless that retailer knowingly sells a children's product\ncontaining a high-priority chemical after the effective date of its\nprohibition for which that retailer has received notification pursuant\nto section 37-0913 of this title.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
